<body>

  <h1>Functional Universe</h1>

  <p>
    We consider a sequence of states $(f_n)$ and define a successor function
    $T(f_n)$ generating the next state.
  </p>

  <p>
    Formally, the evolution operator is given by
    $\mathcal{O}_n = \mathcal{O}(f_n)$,
    where each application advances the system discretely.
  </p>

  <p>
    The proper time increment is written as $(\mathrm{d}\tau)$, and the initial
    epoch occurs at ($t_0 \sim 3.8 \times 10^5$ years).
  </p>

  <h2>Example</h2>

  <p>
    A familiar physical relation appears naturally:
    $E = mc^2$.
  </p>

  <p>
    A representative integral:
  </p>

  $$
  \int_0^\infty e^{-x} \, \mathrm{d}x = 1
  $$

  <hr>

  <p style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;">
